Package org.eclipse.papyrus.sysml14.validation.rules.blocks

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AssociationBlockModelConstraint
    8.3.2.3 Block [1] For an association in which both ends are typed by blocks, the number of ends must be exactly two.
    BindingConnectorSameEndsTypeModelConstraint
    8.3.2.2 Binding Connector [1] The two ends of a binding connector must have either the same type or types that are compatible so that equality of their values can be defined.
    BlockConnectorTwoEndsModelConstraint
    8.3.2.3 Block [2] The number of ends of a connector owned by a block must be exactly two.
    BlockPropertyAssociationEndModelConstraint
    8.3.2.3 Block [4] In the UML metamodel on which SysML is built, a Property that is typed by a block must be defined as an end of an association.
    BlockPropertyCompositeModelConstraint
    8.3.2.3 Block [6] If a property owned by a SysML Block or SysML ValueType is typed by a SysML ValueType, then the aggregation attribute of the property must be «composite.»
    BlockPropertyNoNameModelConstraint
    8.3.2.3 Block [3] In the UML metamodel on which SysML is built, any instance of the Property metaclass that is typed by a block (a Class with the «block» stereotype applied) and which is owned by an Association may not have a name and may not be defined as a navigable owned end of the association.
    BlockSpecializationModelConstraint
    8.3.2.3 Block [8] Any classifier that specializes a Block must also have the Block stereotype or one of its specializations applied.
    ClassifierBehaviorPropertyOnBlockModelConstraint
    8.3.2.5 ClassifierBehaviorProperty [1] ClassifierBehaviorProperty may only be applied to properties owned (not inherited) by blocks that have classifier behaviors.
    ClassifierBehaviorPropertyTypedByModelConstraint
    8.3.2.5 ClassifierBehaviorProperty [3] Properties to which ClassifierBehaviorProperty applied must be typed by the classifier behavior of their owning block or a generalization of the classifier behavior.
    ConnectorPropertyOnlyOnBlockModelConstraint
    8.3.2.6 ConnectorProperty [1] ConnectorProperty may only be applied to properties of classes stereotyped by Block.
    ConnectorPropertyReferOwnedConnectorModelConstraint
    8.3.2.6 ConnectorProperty [2] The connector attribute of the applied stereotype must refer to a connector owned or inherited by a block owning the property on which the stereotype is applied.
    ConnectorPropertySameNameModelConstraint
    8.3.2.6 ConnectorProperty [5] A property stereotyped by ConnectorProperty must have the same name and type as the connector referred to by the connector attribute.
    ConnectorPropertyTypedByAssociationBlockModelConstraint
    8.3.2.6 ConnectorProperty [4] The type of the connector referred to by a connector attribute must be an association class stereotyped by Block.
    DirectedRelationshipPropertyPathRequireSourceContextModelConstraint
    8.3.2.7 DirectedRelationshipPropertyPath [1] source#context must have a value when sourcePropertyPath has a value.
    DirectedRelationshipPropertyPathRequireTargetContextModelConstraint
    8.3.2.7 DirectedRelationshipPropertyPath [1] target#context must have a value when targetPropertyPath has a value.
    DirectedRelationshipPropertyPathSourceFirstModelConstraint
    8.3.2.7 DirectedRelationshipPropertyPath [3] The property in the first position of the sourcePropertyPath list, if any, must be owned by the source#context or one of its generalizations.
    DirectedRelationshipPropertyPathSourceLastModelConstraint
    8.3.2.7 DirectedRelationshipPropertyPath [6] The type of the property at the last position of the sourcePropertyPath list must own or inherit the source of the stereotyped directed relationship.
    DirectedRelationshipPropertyPathTargetFirstModelConstraint
    8.3.2.7 DirectedRelationshipPropertyPath [4] The property in the first position of the targetPropertyPath list, if any, must be owned by the target#context or one of its generalizations.
    DirectedRelationshipPropertyPathTargetLastModelConstraint
    8.3.2.7 DirectedRelationshipPropertyPath [7] The type of the property at the last position of the targetPropertyPath list must own or inherit the target of the stereotyped directed relationship.
    DistributedPropertyTypedByModelConstraint
    8.3.2.8 DistributedProperty [1] The DistributedProperty stereotype may be applied only to properties of classifiers stereotyped by Block or ValueType.
    ElementPropertyPathPropertiesOwnerModelConstraint
    8.3.2.9 ElementPropertyPath [1] The property at each successive position of the propertyPath attribute, following the first position, must be owned by the Block or ValueType that types the property at the immediately preceding position, or a generalization of the Block or ValueType.
    EndPathMultiplicityBoundReferencePropertyModelConstraint
    8.3.2.10 EndPathMultiplicity [1] Properties to which EndPathMultiplicity is applied must be related by redefinition to a property to which BoundReference is applied.
    NestedConnectorEndFirstPropertyModelConstraint
    8.3.2.11 NestedConnectorEnd [1] The first property in propertyPath must be owned by the block that owns the connector, or one of the block's generalizations.
    NestedConnectorEndLastPropertyModelConstraint
    8.3.2.11 NestedConnectorEnd [2] The type of the property at the last position of the propertyPath list must own or inherit the role property of the stereotyped connector end.
    NestedConnectorEndOnlyConnectorEndsModelConstraint
    8.3.2.11 NestedConnectorEnd [3] NestedConnectorEnd may only be applied to connector ends
    ParticipantPropertyEndMultiplicityModelConstraint
    8.3.2.12 ParticipantProperty [6] The property referred to by end must have a multiplicity of 1.
    ParticipantPropertyNoAssociationMemberEndsModelConstraint
    8.3.2.12 ParticipantProperty [2] ParticipantProperty may not be applied to properties that are member ends of an association.
    ParticipantPropertyOnlyAssociationBlockModelConstraint
    8.3.2.12 ParticipantProperty [1] ParticipantProperty may only be applied to properties of association classes stereotyped by Block.
    ParticipantPropertyOnlyNoneAggregationModelConstraint
    8.3.2.12 ParticipantProperty [3] The aggregation of a property stereotyped by ParticipantProperty must be none.
    ParticipantPropertySameEndModelConstraint
    8.3.2.12 ParticipantProperty [4] The end attribute of the applied stereotype must refer to a member end of the association block owning the property on which the stereotype is applied.
    ParticipantPropertySameTypeModelConstraint
    8.3.2.12 ParticipantProperty [5] A property stereotyped by ParticipantProperty must have the same type as the property referred to by the end attribute.
    PropertySpecificTypeMissingNameModelConstraint
    8.3.2.13 PropertySpecificType [2] The name of a classifier to which a PropertySpecificType is applied must be missing.
    PropertySpecificTypeUniquePropertyModelConstraint
    8.3.2.13 PropertySpecificType [1] A classifier to which the PropertySpecificType stereotype is applied must be referenced as the type of one and only one property.
